Stir boiling water into dry gelatin mix in large bowl at least 3 minutes until completely dissolved. Cool 30 minutes at room temperature. Pour milk into medium bowl. Add dry pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk 1 minute. Add to gelatin; stir until well blended. Pour into 13x9-inch pan. Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm. Dip bottom of pan in warm water 15 seconds. Cut into 24 decorative shapes using 2-inch heart-shaped cookie cutters, being careful to cut all the way through gelatin to bottom of pan. Lift JIGGLERS(R) from pan. Store in tightly covered container in refrigerator.